The complexities of this algorithm lie in the mathematical principles of pitch class set theory, which involve modular arithmetic and set theory. To determine the interval vector, we first assign a unique number to each note in the scale using modular arithmetic, which ensures that notes in different octaves are assigned the same number. We then use set theory operations to calculate the intervals between adjacent notes in the scale.
